ces the unexpected and far-reaching ramifications of seemingly inconsequential actions, while reminding us all of the importance of communication.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 04. Okt 2022) 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / General.2bisacsh  aMao Dun Literary Prize winner.1 aGoldblatt, Howard, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLin, Sylvia Li-chun, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRojas, Carlos, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDuke University Press Complete eBook-Package 2018z97831106963320 cprintz978082237068040uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780822371885423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780822371885/original  a978-3-11-069633-2  Duke University Press Complete eBook-Package 2018b2018  aEBA_DUK_ALL  aEBA_DUK_EALL  aEBA_DUK_SSHALL  aGBV-deGruyter-alles